sec.p:
In the MultiPatch module, a wall is subdivided into n patches, indexed j. Each patch is assigned properties including a reference area ApRef,j (Fig 6) and tissue volume Vp,j. Tissue properties, and hence fibre Cauchy stress and strain, are allowed to vary between patches, and so Eq 2 no longer holds throughout the wall. To solve the related equilibrium equations, wall tension Tw is linearized about a working point corresponding to the wall area at zero wall tension (A0,w), i.e. wall area if the tissue would experience no external load;




Tw(Aw)≈dTwdAw(Aw−A0,w).


